author: Eileen Sullivan, Associated Press
title: Watchdog confirms Secret Service director's changing story
text: Photo: Andrew Harnik, AP In this photo taken Oct. 5, 2015, U.S. Secret Service Director Joseph Clancy speaks in Washington. The Homeland Security Department's internal watchdog says Clancy knew earlier than he originally stated about a rumor that agents were digging up dirt on a congressman who had been critical of the agency. In this photo taken Oct. 5, 2015, U.S. Secret Service Director... WASHINGTON (AP) — First, Secret Service Director Joseph Clancy told federal watchdog investigators that he heard a rumor on April 1 about a congressman's failed attempt years earlier to work at the agency.
